data.title: Significant "rave fences" levitating with Kite at Dalhalla 2023
data.meta_description: Kite perfoming at "Dalhalla" Sweden 2023, with lighting effects that were created by the use of 10 Winch10 .
data.meta_site_name: Significant "rave fences" levitating with Kite at Dalhalla 2023
data.text:
Sweden's most majestic venue "Dalhalla" is located north of Stockholm at the bottom of an old limestone quarry. The Swedish synth-pop band "Kite" performed a one time concert at the venue, putting in their visual ambitions, with astonishing light design from Swedish lightdesigner, Anders Heberling.

Anders Heberling designed the never seen before "Levitating Rave Fences."

Four rows of five construction fences, with each fence suspended by 2 x Winch10. Each fence had 3 LED bars mounted on the bottom rod, which together with the Winch10 made for an interesting sight.

40 units of our Winch10 were put into use in this design, and gave endless opportunities for designing different formations, and creating beutiful kinetic movements.

Watch the video above of the "Rave Fences" at Dalhalla.

(Photos by, Ben Fee)
